pr_title: feat: Authorization for performing pod operations by Casbin enforcer
pr_body:
@hsluoyz , As mentioned I started working for the plugin. At present, I'm working on to define the roles for performing different pod operations on k8s.  
In the initial phase, I would like to validate the users based on their roles to perform operations on pods. The work for the initial phase will be reviewed from this PR. I might need some help inorder to make it completely functional. 

Onece it is over, I will then move to extend its functionality for the cluster roles and we can significantly bring more changes later for the plugin. 

Looking for a detailed review.

pr_body:
@hsluoyz ,
Work done:-
- Removed the background from the logo
- Changed the link to the docs
- Added basic tests for server and webhook

Next, I will try to add tests for cheking the policy and validation. 

While, I was running the deployment file on a minikube cluster, I encountered few bugs which were caused due to migration of v1beta to v1. Since, v1beta is now deprecated, I would be following this [guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/using-api/deprecation-guide/#deployment-v116) to fix those in my next PR.

@hsluoyz ,
Added the CI for build, lints, tests and for semantic release.
Added goreportcard,coverall and CI build badges for Readme
Fixed the minor bugs.

As of now, build is passing successfully. However, the lints are failing because of some tests related issues. I also have to add an e2e test to check complete working of our application. 

I will be doing these tasks in my next PR.
